{
    "level": "sentence",
    "abstract": [
        {
            "text": "The Dalitz-plot of the decay D 0 \u2192 \u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 \u03c0 0 measured by the BABAR collaboration shows the structure of a final state having quantum numbers I G J PC = 0 \u2212 0 \u2212\u2212 . ",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "An isospin analysis of this Dalitz-plot finds that the fraction of the I = 0 contribution is about 96%. ",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1
        },
        {
            "text": "This high I = 0 contribution is unexpected because the weak interaction violates the isospin.",
            "paragraph_rank": 1,
            "section_rank": 1
        }
    ],
    "body_text": [
        {
            "text": "INTRODUCTION",
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "This communication reports the results of the analysis of the Cabibbo suppressed decay 2",
            "section": "INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 2,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "(1) made by the BABAR collaboration. ",
            "section": "INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The BABAR detector [1] measured the e + e \u2212 annihilations at the PEP-II collider. ",
            "section": "INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 2,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 19,
                    "end": 22,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b0",
                    "text": "[1]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Most of the data were taken at the \u03d2(4S) resonance to study the B mesons. ",
            "section": "INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The detector measured also the decays of the charm mesons and baryons generated by the decay of the B mesons or by the continuum, i.e. by the e + e \u2212 annihilations into qq.",
            "section": "INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 3,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The charged tracks were measured by a silicon vertex tracker and by a drift chamber, and identified by a ringimaging Cherenkov detector. ",
            "section": "INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The photons were measured by an elctromagnetic calorimeter made of CSI(Tl) crystals. ",
            "section": "INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The magnetic field of 1.5 T was generated by a superconducting solenoid. ",
            "section": "INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "The iron of the flux return was instrumented by RPCs and LSTs for measuring the muons.",
            "section": "INTRODUCTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 4,
            "section_rank": 2
        },
        {
            "text": "DATA COLLECTION",
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The data used in this analysis include 288 fb \u22121 taken at the \u03d2(4S) resonance and 27 fb \u22121 collected below the resonance.",
            "section": "DATA COLLECTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 5,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The cuts applied for selecting the D 0 \u2192 \u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 \u03c0 0 candidates are [2]: ",
            "section": "DATA COLLECTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 68,
                    "end": 71,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b1",
                    "text": "[2]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "(i) charged tracks with p T > 100 MeV/c; ",
            "section": "DATA COLLECTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "(ii) particle identification compatibile with a charged pion; ",
            "section": "DATA COLLECTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 6,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The Dalitz-plot of the events selected with these cuts is shown in Fig. 1. ",
            "section": "DATA COLLECTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 67,
                    "end": 73,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "text": "Fig. 1"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "It was already published in Refs. ",
            "section": "DATA COLLECTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "[3,4]. ",
            "section": "DATA COLLECTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 0,
                    "end": 3,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b2",
                    "text": "[3,"
                },
                {
                    "start": 3,
                    "end": 5,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b3",
                    "text": "4]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "It contains 44 780 \u00b1 250 D 0 decays and an estimated contamination of 830 \u00b1 250 events. ",
            "section": "DATA COLLECTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "The contamination was evaluated using the sideband 1930",
            "section": "DATA COLLECTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 7,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "This Dalitz-plot shows three \u03c1 bands and has low density at the centre and on the three diagonals. ",
            "section": "DATA COLLECTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3
        },
        {
            "text": "This structure is typical of a \u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 \u03c0 0 final state with I G J P = 0 \u2212 0 \u2212 [5]. ",
            "section": "DATA COLLECTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 78,
                    "end": 81,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b4",
                    "text": "[5]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The same properties were also visible in the CLEO analysis of the same decay [6]. ",
            "section": "DATA COLLECTION",
            "paragraph_rank": 8,
            "section_rank": 3,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 77,
                    "end": 80,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b5",
                    "text": "[6]"
                }
