        },
        {
            "text": "we obtain B(D 0 \u2192 3\u03c0 0 ) = B(D 0 \u2192 \u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 \u03c0 0 ) ;0> = (8.3 \u00b1 0.8) \u00d7 10 \u22125 .",
            "paragraph_rank": 28,
            "section_rank": 11
        },
        {
            "text": ".010 \u00b1 0.021 16.2 \u00b1 0.6 \u00b1 0.4 26.2 \u00b1 0.5 \u00b1 1.1 \u03c1(770) \u2212 \u03c0 + 0.588 \u00b1 0.014 \u00b1 0.005 \u22122.0 \u00b1 0.6 \u00b1 0.6 34.6 \u00b1 0.8 \u00b1 0.3 \u03c1(1450) + \u03c0 \u2212 0.033 \u00b1 0.021 \u00b1 0.036 \u2212146 \u00b1 18",
            "paragraph_rank": 29,
            "section_rank": 12
        },
        {
            "text": "The phase of the state |0(1); 0 > is fixed at 0 \u2022 .",
            "paragraph_rank": 30,
            "section_rank": 13
        },
        {
            "text": "INTERPRETATION AND PREDICTIONS",
            "section_rank": 15
        },
        {
            "text": "A \u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 \u03c0 0 final state generated by a pseudoscalar meson decay has J P = 0 \u2212 , G-parity \u22121, and charge conjugation C = G(\u22121) I . ",
            "section": "INTERPRETATION AND PREDICTIONS",
            "paragraph_rank": 31,
            "section_rank": 15
        },
        {
            "text": "The isospin states |0(1); 0 > and 2 (1); 0 > have CP = +1 and the other three states with I = 1 have CP = \u22121. ",
            "section": "INTERPRETATION AND PREDICTIONS",
            "paragraph_rank": 31,
            "section_rank": 15,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 36,
                    "end": 39,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b0",
                    "text": "(1)"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Therefore, the results shown in Table II tell us that the decay D 0 \u2192 \u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 \u03c0 0 proceeds for (98.11 \u00b1 0.11)% via the CP = +1 eigenstate",
            "section": "INTERPRETATION AND PREDICTIONS",
            "paragraph_rank": 31,
            "section_rank": 15,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 32,
                    "end": 40,
                    "type": "table",
                    "text": "Table II"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "The tree graphs shown in Fig. 2 do not predict the dominance of a pure isospin state. ",
            "section": "INTERPRETATION AND PREDICTIONS",
            "paragraph_rank": 32,
            "section_rank": 15,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 25,
                    "end": 31,
                    "type": "figure",
                    "text": "Fig. 2"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "Then, if the I = 0 dominance is not coincidental, there should be a physical explanation. ",
            "section": "INTERPRETATION AND PREDICTIONS",
            "paragraph_rank": 32,
            "section_rank": 15
        },
        {
            "text": "A possible interpretation is that the I = 0 dominance is due to a final state interaction with an I G J PC = 0 \u2212 0 \u2212\u2212 meson that resonates with the four quark generated by the D 0 decay. ",
            "section": "INTERPRETATION AND PREDICTIONS",
            "paragraph_rank": 32,
            "section_rank": 15
        },
        {
            "text": "Such a meson must be exotic because a qq pair cannot have these quantum number. ",
            "section": "INTERPRETATION AND PREDICTIONS",
            "paragraph_rank": 32,
            "section_rank": 15
        },
        {
            "text": "It could be a state 2q2q.",
            "section": "INTERPRETATION AND PREDICTIONS",
            "paragraph_rank": 32,
            "section_rank": 15
        },
        {
            "text": "If this interpretation is right, this meson should also have other decays. ",
            "section": "INTERPRETATION AND PREDICTIONS",
            "paragraph_rank": 33,
            "section_rank": 15
        },
        {
            "text": "The pricipal candidates are the final states 2\u03c0 + 2\u03c0 \u2212 \u03c0 0 and \u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 3\u03c0 0 because the analysis of the D 0 \u2192 \u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 \u03c0 0 found a non negligible contributions of the channels \u03c1(1450)\u03c0 and \u03c1(1700)\u03c0, and the mesons \u03c1(1450) and \u03c1(1700) decay also in 4\u03c0. ",
            "section": "INTERPRETATION AND PREDICTIONS",
            "paragraph_rank": 33,
            "section_rank": 15
        },
        {
            "text": "Futhermore, it is possible that this meson could also decay into KK\u03c0.",
            "section": "INTERPRETATION AND PREDICTIONS",
            "paragraph_rank": 33,
            "section_rank": 15
        },
        {
            "text": "CONCLUSIONS",
            "section_rank": 16
        },
        {
            "text": "We see a strange behaviour in the D 0 \u2192 \u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 \u03c0 0 Dalitz-plot: this decay is dominated by the I = 0 final state [3,4]. ",
            "section": "CONCLUSIONS",
            "paragraph_rank": 34,
            "section_rank": 16,
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 114,
                    "end": 117,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b2",
                    "text": "[3,"
                },
                {
                    "start": 117,
                    "end": 119,
                    "type": "bibr",
                    "ref_id": "b3",
                    "text": "4]"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "text": "We take this as a hint of someting interesting that deserves further studies. ",
            "section": "CONCLUSIONS",
            "paragraph_rank": 34,
            "section_rank": 16
        },
        {
            "text": "We need to analyze the decays D 0 \u2192 KK\u03c0 and D 0 \u2192 5\u03c0 to understand if the I = 0 dominance in D 0 \u2192 \u03c0 + \u03c0 \u2212 \u03c0 0 is coincidental or it is a general rule not predicted by the standard model.",
            "section": "CONCLUSIONS",
            "paragraph_rank": 34,
            "section_rank": 16
        },
